cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper presents a corpus for named entity recognition in Finnish news articles. The task of named entity recognition falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP), which is typically covered by the arXiv sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also presents experiments using rule-based and deep learning systems, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence, covered by the arXiv sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the use of deep learning models for named entity recognition suggests a potential overlap with the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
